### Session Tracking (sessions/ directory)

**Individual session files with daemon names, role, and timing metadata**

Each development session creates a separate file:
- **Format:** `YYYY-mm-dd.HH:MM:SS.role.name.task-summary.md`
- **Names:** Daemon names from mythology (Lucifer, Azazel, Mephistopheles, Seraphina, Iblis, Ravana, Loki, etc.)
- **Disambiguation:** If name used before, append roman numeral (`-ii`, `-iii`, `-iv`)
- **Metadata:** Date, times, role, daemon name, status (completed/failed/aborted/in-progress)
- **Content:** Objective, work log, files changed, outcomes, next steps

Session tracking provides:
- Self-documenting filenames (all key info visible)
- Chronological work history
- Easy discovery by date/role/name/task
- Complete context for each development session
- Fun thematic naming convention

**Use when:** Starting a session (create file), during session (update work log), ending session (mark complete)

**REQUIRED:** Every agent must create a session file at start and update at end!

**See:** `.opencode/sessions/README.md` for template, daemon name examples, and guidelines


